    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Implausible in Iran</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lawrence Kuznick letter says Iranian Jew's alleged confession to spying for 'Zionist regime' is completely implausible, given that Jews do not refer to Israel in this way (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your May 11 news article about the 13 Iranian Jews on trial for spying stated that one of the defendants made a full confession outside the courtroom, saying, ''I admit to spying on behalf of the Zionist regime.''</p>
        <p>I, as a Jew, have never heard another Jew refer to Israel or its government as ''the Zionist regime.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your May 11 news article about the 13 Iranian Jews on trial for spying stated that one of the defendants made a full confession outside the courtroom, saying, ''I admit to spying on behalf of the Zionist regime.''</p>
        <p>I, as a Jew, have never heard another Jew refer to Israel or its government as ''the Zionist regime.''</p>
        <p>If this matter were not so serious, with extremely dire consequences awaiting these unfortunate men, the whole affair would be laughable. It is not. But it is an insult to everybody's intelligence.</p>
        <p>LAWRENCE KUZNICK  New York, May 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
